"{\"opportunities\":[{\"name\":\"Supporting Grassroots Music\",\"organization\":[\"Department for Culture, Media and Sport\",\"UK Government\",\"National Lottery Project Grants\"],\"details\":[\"An additional ring-fenced budget of \u00a31.5 million is available within Project Grants specifically to support the grassroots live music sector.\",\"The grassroots music sector includes rehearsal and recording studios, venues, festivals, and promoters.\",\"Grassroots music is crucial for developing skills, testing new ideas, and engaging with audiences both locally and nationally.\",\"The sector supports talent development and facilitates musical experiences across the country.\",\"Funded by the Department for Culture, Media and Sport as part of the UK Government\u2019s Creative Industries Sector Vision.\",\"A further \u00a32.5 million has been invested to support Grassroots Music for this financial year as part of this initiative.\",\"The programme supports rehearsal and recording studios, festivals, promoters, as well as venues for live and electronic music performance.\",\"Follows a previous \u00a35 million investment covering November 2023 to April 2025.\"],\"eligibility\":[\"Open to grassroots music venues and promoters.\"],\"application_requirements\":[\"Applicants should familiarize themselves with all relevant guidance documents and information sheets before starting their application.\"],\"other\":[\"Claire Mera-Nelson is the Director of Music at Arts Council who explores support for grassroots music through further funding from DCMS.\"]}]}"